Brazil Stock Movers: B2W Varejo, Banco do Brasil, PDG Realty

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-09-01T20:59:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-01/brazil-stock-movers-b2w-varejo-banco-do-brasil-pdg-realty.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:45 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index rose 2.9 percent to 58,118.20.  B2W Cia. Global do Varejo (BTOW3 BS),  Brazil ’s largest
online retailer, surged 8.4 percent to 17.40 reais, its highest
price since July 6, as Brazil’s central bank yesterday cut its
benchmark Selic rate. Shares rose as high as 11 percent.  Banco do Brasil SA (BBAS3)  (BBAS3 BS),  Latin America ’s biggest bank
by assets, gained 6.1 percent to 28.35 reais, its highest price
in almost two months, as investors expect the central bank’s
decision to cut  interest rates  will spark an increase in
consumer and business loans.  PDG Realty SA Empreendimentos & Participacoes (PDGR3 BS),
Brazil’s biggest homebuilder by revenue, gained for the fifth
consecutive trading session, rising 7.3 percent to 8.40 reais as
investors anticipate that lower borrowing rates will spur more
real estate purchases. Shares have risen 26 percent since Aug.
25.  To contact the reporter on this story:
